result.execSummary:
The defendant Ashley M Barrientes-Womack was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Retail Theft - Intentionally Take (<=$500) AMENDED FROM RETAIL THEFT-INTENTIONALLY TAKE >$500-$5000 [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 943.50(1m)(b).
  • Possess Drug Paraphernalia, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 961.573(1).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

miscConds.notes: Defendant must pay all outstanding fees and court obligations including costs of supervision during the term of probation.   If supervision is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant and in favor of restitution victims and governmental entities for the balance due.  Collections may include income assignment.

No alcohol or controlled substances except by prescription. Random UA's are authorized. Any counseling deemed appropriate by agent including maintaining treatment defendant is already enrolled in. Must obtain and maintain full time verifiable employment or attend school full time or a combination of both equal to full time. No contact with Pick N Save on S. Green Bay Rd. No contact with co-defendant. Do not associate with any known drug dealers or users. Defendant must obey all rules and regulations while on probation.

timeConds.notes: per week when not employed full time, attending school full time or a combination of both equal to full time.
